issue.title: amp-lightbox-gallery: issue when only 2 images
issue.body:
When triggering an amp-lightbox-gallery that **only has 2 images**, it's not possible to swipe to the right, and swiping to the left has a flickering effect and it's not consistently displaying the image How to reproduce it: Go to the playground for amp-lightbox-gallery https://playground.amp.dev/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fpreview.amp.dev%2Fdocumentation%2Fexamples%2Fcomponents%2Famp-lightbox-gallery&mode=Galaxy+S5 and leave only 2 images, something like this: ```

Lorem ....

Lorem ....

``` Reproduce it using Google Chrome tools, trigger the device toolbar, and choose iphone 6/7/8 for instance. Arrows seem to work though

comment.body: So, if I have 2 pictures on a page, that cannot be put inside an amp-crousel v0.2, I'm stuck with this issue. Brilliant!

issue.title: Granular User Consent for CMP
issue.body:
### Description

Currently AMP has provided granular choice for purposes based on this [docs](https://amp.dev/documentation/examples/user-consent/granular_user_consent/ ) It works for client AMP website but CMP works inside an `iframe` where we can't access and update purpose statuses. 

It will be nice to provide `purposeStatuses` also to `iframe` and to store this object in user browser in `<cmp name>:amp-consent`. Also allow CMP to return this object back to `amphtml` from iframe and consent api. 

### Alternatives Considered

We could have a granular choice for vendor and purposes inside CMP and return additional consent but in this case clients need to decode it and it will be an issue for most of clients that would like to use `amphtml` tags to block content based on user choice. 

### Additional Context

_No response_

issue.title: Investigate Circle CI Unit Tests Freeze
issue.body:
Unit tests fail often on CircleCI with an output timeout, but only when running on `main` (i.e., after merging a PR)

e.g., https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/ampproject/amphtml/29255/workflows/a2aba312-d359-47a9-ba64-c6759cb9af15/jobs/625180
![image](https://github.com/ampproject/amphtml/assets/1839738/a752731b-569c-4e2a-ac7d-66c197468e8a)

These failures occur often enough that they're causing [close to 40%](https://app.circleci.com/insights/github/ampproject/amphtml/workflows/CircleCI/overview) of CI runs on `main` to fail (!)

 I attempted to add debugging output for when unit tests are running for too long (#39501) but this code doesn't seem to produce any output, which makes me suspect that this might be some sort of stdout pipe buffer issue. I'll continue to investigate and try different ideas until I knock this down

issue.title: Granular consent for CMP
issue.body:
### Description

Currently AMP has provided granular choice for purposes based on this [docs](https://amp.dev/documentation/examples/user-consent/granular_user_consent/ ) It works for client AMP website but CMP works inside an `iframe` where we can't access and update purpose statuses. 

It will be nice to provide `purposeStatuses` also to `iframe` and to store this object in user browser in `<cmp name>:amp-consent`. Also allow CMP to return this object back to `amphtml` from iframe and consent api. 

### Alternatives Considered

We could have a granular choice for vendor and purposes inside CMP and return additional consent but in this case clients need to decode it and it will be an issue for most of clients that would like to use `amphtml` tags to block content based on user choice. 

### Additional Context

_No response_

issue.title: INTENT TO IMPLEMENT: amp-video-interface API: integration with 3rd party video player Connatix

labels.name: INTENT TO IMPLEMENT
labels.description: Proposes implementation of a significant new feature.  https://bit.ly/amp-contribute-code

issue.body: Hi – I’m Jimmy from [Connatix](https://connatix.com/) and we are a video player company for publishers. We have an amp player built with amp components and would love to use the [amp-video-docking](https://amp.dev/documentation/components/amp-video-docking) functionality, which notes being a “supported video player” as a pre-requisite. What is the process of integrating with this [amp-video-interface API](https://github.com/ampproject/amphtml/blob/main/docs/spec/amp-video-interface.md) (i.e., be certified by amp)? Thanks
